parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to potential injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
passenger airbag light is off or flashing
passenger seatbelt light is flashing
error codes B1448
or others related to OCS sensor mat failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door handle can cause difficulty in exiting the vehicle in an emergency situation, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Door handle comes off
inside door handle comes off
door is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light can cause reduced visibility to other drivers, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake lights do not illuminate all the time when engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle sways in the back due to rusted control arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause obstruction of the driver's vision, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down or does not stay in the up position
obstructing the driver's view; the visor hangs straight down or at an angle
blocking the driver's vision; the visor suddenly drops down while driving
causing a startle effect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Caliper Sticking and Premature Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of rear brake calipers can cause premature wear of brake pads and rotors, leading to brake failure and accidents.
symptoms: Rear brake pads wear out prematurely
rear brake rotors show excessive wear
grinding or screeching noise from rear brakes
rear brake caliper sticking or seizing.

symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear of brake pads and rotors can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
